The paper deals with lower bounds for distributed graph algorithms, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The specific focus on bandwidth limitations and the CONGEST model suggests that Distributed Systems (cs.DS) and Computer Communication Networks (cs.NI) may also be relevant sub-categories. The use of graph theory and algorithms suggests that Computational Complexity (cs.CC) may also be a relevant sub-category. Finally, the potential implications for various settings of distributed computing suggest that Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) may also be a relevant sub-category.
